{"word":"Bethsaida","slug":"bethsaida","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Bethsaida</b> <a href=\"#/G966\">G966</a> <br/> 1. A city of Galilee<br/> - The city of Philip, Andrew, and Peter<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=43&chapter=1&verse=44'>Joh 1:44</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=43&chapter=12&verse=21'>Joh 12:21</a> <br/> - Jesus visits<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=41&chapter=6&verse=45'>Mar 6:45</a> <br/> - Jesus cures a blind man in<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=41&chapter=8&verse=22'>Mar 8:22</a> <br/> - Jesus prophesies against<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=11&verse=21'>Mat 11:21</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=42&chapter=10&verse=13'>Luk 10:13</a> <br/> 2. Desert of, east of the sea of Galilee, Jesus feeds five thousand people in<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=42&chapter=9&verse=10'>Luk 9:10</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=14&verse=13'>Mat 14:13</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=41&chapter=6&verse=32'>Mar 6:32</a>"}]}